title: Oops! Varun Dhawan couldn't cast his vote in BMC Election! Here's why...
text:
Varun Dhawan 
Bollywood actor Varun Dhawan couldn't cast his vote in the BMC Election 2017 on Tuesday. The 'Badrinath Ki Dulhaniya' actor reached his poll booth in Bandra, Mumbai but wasn't able to vote.
Varun Dhawan told reporters present at the polling booth that he couldn't vote as his name was missing from the voter list. Varun Dhawan said he was upset and that he found it bizarre that his name is missing as he had voted last year. Varun Dhawan added that he will find out from the Election Commission why his name isn't there.
